1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,091
YJM lives in a new home.

2
00:00:03,921 --> 00:00:09,411
In every big decision, the mind battles with itself, to act or not to act,

3
00:00:09,521 --> 00:00:11,411
to do or not to do.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,771
Here's how one young fellow elected to act and reaped big rewards.

5
00:00:17,601 --> 00:00:21,970
J.M.'s situation is similar to that of a million other young men.

6
00:00:22,081 --> 00:00:27,731
He is in his twenties, has a wife and child, and still has only a modest income.

7
00:00:28,161 --> 00:00:31,330
Mr. and Mrs. J.M. lived in a small apartment.

8
00:00:31,441 --> 00:00:33,330
Both wanted a new home.

9
00:00:33,521 --> 00:00:39,330
They wanted the advantage of more space, cleaner surroundings, a place for the youngster to play,

10
00:00:39,361 --> 00:00:42,690
and a chance to build up equity in their own property.

11
00:00:43,121 --> 00:00:47,090
But there was a hitch to buying a new home, the down payment.

12
00:00:47,361 --> 00:00:53,651
One day, as J.M. was writing next month's rent check, he became very disgusted with himself.

13
00:00:54,001 --> 00:00:59,330
He observed that the rent payment was as much as monthly payments on a new home.

14
00:00:59,921 --> 00:01:05,090
J.M. called his wife and said, How would you like to buy a new home next week?

15
00:01:05,361 --> 00:01:06,690
What's got into you?

16
00:01:06,721 --> 00:01:07,491
she asked.

17
00:01:07,681 --> 00:01:09,011
Why make jokes?

18
00:01:09,041 --> 00:01:10,210
You know we can't.

19
00:01:10,321 --> 00:01:13,171
We haven't even got the money for the down payment.

20
00:01:13,521 --> 00:01:15,570
but J.M. was determined.

21
00:01:15,841 --> 00:01:21,251
There are hundreds of thousands of couples like us who are going to buy a new home someday,

22
00:01:21,361 --> 00:01:23,570
but only about half of them ever do.

23
00:01:23,841 --> 00:01:26,131
Something always comes up to stop them.

24
00:01:26,401 --> 00:01:28,210
We're going to buy a home.

25
00:01:28,481 --> 00:01:32,450
I don't know yet how we'll raise the down payment, but we will.

26
00:01:33,121 --> 00:01:41,491
Well, the next week, they found a house they both liked, quite unpretentious but nice, for $1,200 down.

27
00:01:41,841 --> 00:01:46,690
Now, the obstacle was to find a way to raise $1,200.

28
00:01:46,881 --> 00:01:55,330
J.M. knew he couldn't borrow it through the usual channels, for this would encumber his credit so that he couldn't get a mortgage for the sale price.

29
00:01:55,921 --> 00:01:58,531
Where there's a will, there's always a way.

30
00:01:58,641 --> 00:02:01,411
Suddenly, J.M. got a brainstorm.

31
00:02:01,681 --> 00:02:07,810
Why not contact the builder and work out a private loan arrangement for $1,200?

32
00:02:07,921 --> 00:02:09,731
This J.M. did.

33
00:02:10,081 --> 00:02:15,011
At first, the builder was cold to the idea, but J.M. persisted.

34
00:02:15,201 --> 00:02:15,665
Finally, it was agreed.
